name: International Conference on Developments in Language Theory
summary:
DLT, the International Conference on Developments in Language Theory is an academic conference in the field 
of computer science
held annually under the auspices of the European Association for Theoretical Computer Science. Like most theoretical computer science conferences its contributions are strongly peer-reviewed; the articles appear in proceedings published in Springer Lecture Notes in Computer Science.
